16 shall be appointed at large and, at the time of the appointment,
17 have had at least five (5) years' continuous practical experience in
18 the practice of barbering in this state; one member shall be a lay
19 person; one member shall be an administrator of a licensed private
20 cosmetology school; one member shall be an administrator of a
21 licensed barber school; and one member shall be an administrator of
22 a public school licensed to teach cosmetology or barbering.
23 4. No two members shall be graduates of the same cosmetology
24 school, nor shall they be organizers of or promote the organization
